   "description": "Axel Rudolf Hall was a Swedish architect born on August 4th, 1904 in Glimåkra, Kristianstad county. He is known for his work in Gothenburg and throughout Sweden, as well as his extensive travels throughout Denmark, Norway, Germany, Belgium, Holland, Austria, and Italy. In addition to his architectural work, Hall contributed to the areas of property divisions, taxation, and forestry management. He passed away in 1975."
